n\times n
\operatorname{Span}\{v_{\lambda} \} 
v_{\lambda}
\lambda
 C_p=\begin{bmatrix} 0 & 1 & 0 &\cdots & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 1 &\cdots & 0 \\ \vdots&\vdots &\vdots&\ddots&\vdots\\ 0 & 0 & 0 &\cdots &1 \\ -\alpha_0 &-\alpha_1 &-\alpha_2 &\cdots&-\alpha_{n-1} \end{bmatrix} 
 v_{\lambda} =  \begin{bmatrix} 1 \\ \lambda\\ \lambda^{2} \\ \vdots\\ \lambda^{n-1} \end{bmatrix}. 
C_p{\bf x}=\lambda {\bf x}
{\bf x}=(x_1,\dots,x_n)^T
x_2=\lambda x_1
x_3=\lambda x_2
\dots
x_n=\lambda x_{n-1}
x_2=\lambda x_1
x_3=\lambda^2 x_1
\dots
x_n=\lambda^{n-1}x_1
{\bf x}=x_1v_{\lambda}
